OL,3,CThe 96-year-old multi-millionaire
OL,4,Cliving in hotel for two years
OL,6,F"The other homes can't have a ballroom
OL,7,Fwhere you can entertain 60 people at a
OL,8,Fdinner. Here you can."
OL,10,FStuart moved to their first property
OL,11,Fin the 1960s, after becoming one of
OL,12,Fthe very first people to be granted
OL,13,F'high-value residency'.
OL,15,FThroughout his business career, Stuart
OL,16,Fhas rubbed shoulders with high-profile
OL,17,Fpoliticians and former presidents,
OL,18,Fincluding Nelson Mandela.
